        "id": 1003211
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-11-18T00:56:41Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I prefer to allow any data in the database and only enforce constraints in this layer. It makes adding/modifying/removing constraints easier, e.g. we can enforce a new constraint going forward by validating data going in without applying it to thousands of existing entries. Labs wants more consistency going forward but doesn\u0027t want to rename everything that already exists.",
