      },
      "lineNbr": 106,
      "author": {
        "id": 1003211
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-11-18T00:56:41Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027m worried about using SQL statements that are too complex, especially because we don\u0027t have a good test for this (current tests just assert that some SQL statement was executed, a proper test would use an in-memory database to actually execute the SQL and we\u0027d assert the state of the database after running the test, which would test that the SQL itself was correct not just the Go).\n\nAt any rate, I\u0027m not sure I understand how find_in_set will be useful here. The doc says it finds the position of str in strlist. That\u0027s still only one position it will find.\n\nWhy not just batch as:\nDELETE FROM datacenters WHERE id \u003d x OR id \u003d y OR id \u003d z\n\nn.b. the number of datacenters is small and this request isn\u0027t time sensitive, which is why I skipped batching for now.",
