      },
      "lineNbr": 119,
      "author": {
        "id": 1114299
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-11-17T16:38:04Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "if we have a service per config entity, it means we have one method per service. This requires writing more code.\nAny reason not have just one service for all resources? or at least one service for resources defined in config and one service for resources living in database? not a part of this CL",
      "revId": "4ac64e9835cdc5fa6b35137797a21dd99ad2254e",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "7e462e83_4a00b1fd",
        "filename": "machine-db/appengine/model/datacenters/datacenters.go",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 119,
      "author": {
        "id": 1003211
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-11-18T00:56:41Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I can make one service if you prefer. Currently everything is grouped together, so if you look at datacenters.proto you can see the service with its one method and all corresponding Message definitions. If I have only one service then RPC-related messages won\u0027t be in the same file as the related service definition anymore (unless we put everything in the same file, but that might be too much since there are datacenters, racks, switches, operating systems, VLANs, and platform types). Still, I don\u0027t mind either way. I can refactor when I add some other service.",
      "parentUuid": "dcf36d9d_99ccfbea",
